This paper deals with the problem of clustering large numbers of face images, which is a common task in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new clustering algorithm that achieves better results than other well-known algorithms, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with the challenge of scalability, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also mentions the use of external and internal cluster quality measures, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
